				<div class="comment-head">
					<span class="name"><a href='http://gomiam.wordpress.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>gomiam</a></span>
											<span class="date"><a href="http://violentmetaphors.com/2014/03/25/parents-you-are-being-lied-to/comment-page-15/#comment-63360" title="Permalink">September 21, 2014 at 11:02 am</a></span>
						<span class="edit"></span>
									</div><!-- /.comment-head -->

				
				<div class="comment-text">
					<p>Yes, a neurological syndrome has managed to show the day after the vaccination. If they had been taken to be vaccinated a week later the boy would have been mute for a week already.<br />
What you are trying to do here is called a &#8220;post hoc, ergo propter hoc&#8221; fallacy: event B happens after event A, so event A caused event B. What you don&#8217;t take into account is that neurological problems don&#8217;t show up in one day.</p>
				</div><!-- /.comment-text -->

